      <title>APIs</title> 
<section>
  <title>Programming Model Overview</title>
  <para>The CAS service allows for managing fine grained access policy of
resources in a VO. The service has a back end database that stores data
about users/resources/actions and the associated rights. It provides
an administrative interface for managing the data and a query
interface that allows users to retrieve this information. One of
the operations in the query interface includes a means to get a signed
SAML assertion that the client can present to a resource for
authorization purposes.</para>
</section>

